{"TopicId":175679,"ForumId":46,"TopicTitle":"Imgur issues on Edge","CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T14:02:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T14:02:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote, this only seems to effect Microsoft Edge, I guess I\u0027ll have to switch to Chrome for writing now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo... when I write mission report chapters I usually do them on the forum itself, which involves going to an album on imgur, right clicking an image, pressing copy, and ctrl-v ing it into the forum.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept it\u0027s not working right now. I\u0027ve copied an image, and it should show up here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/CN0iIsQ.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022background-attachment:scroll;background-color:transparent;background-image:none;background-repeat:repeat;border-bottom-color:rgb(119,137,255);border-bottom-style:none;border-bottom-width:0px;border-left-color:rgb(119,137,255);border-left-style:none;border-left-width:0px;border-right-color:rgb(119,137,255);border-right-style:none;border-right-width:0px;border-top-color:rgb(119,137,255);border-top-style:none;border-top-width:0px;color:rgb(119,137,255);font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:14px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:0px;text-align:center;text-decoration:underline;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;\u0022 title=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022CN0iIsQ.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/CN0iIsQ.png\u0022 style=\u0022background-attachment:scroll;background-color:transparent;background-image:none;background-repeat:repeat;border-bottom-color:rgb(119,137,255);border-bottom-style:none;border-bottom-width:0px;border-left-color:rgb(119,137,255);border-left-style:none;border-left-width:0px;border-right-color:rgb(119,137,255);border-right-style:none;border-right-width:0px;border-top-color:rgb(119,137,255);border-top-style:none;border-top-width:0px;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;height:410px;line-height:14px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:0px;max-width:728px;min-height:410px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:0px;vertical-align:baseline;width:728px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt just says \u0022pasted as rich text, place as plain text instead?\u0022 and doesn\u0027t show up. There is a faint grey outline clipping into everything else on which I cannot select\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: What the what? After I post it it shows up, but not while posting. Hmm. Still an issue, and it\u0027s too small.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can copy the link, and it will show up like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022CN0iIsQ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/CN0iIsQ.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBUT it\u0027s width limited, I cannot make it any wider, and on my monitor it\u0027s only half to 2/3 the width of the screen, so it makes it weird trying to read my own stories when the text goes beyond the image.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI found a way to make them bigger by going into google drawings and repasting the picture here, and I can make them big, but on small monitors they distort because the height and width are no longer linked.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022A49v0RGqHPTy2DDTo9L4ij9vv1BYy3vcMUIkcKfevMAheTDVCxlnTlbB-7Ueb6dlHSjnF3Ig1n7GI37RRqQIAce8QUI2b-9JMM_ixl9998aGwwn3OxnUCqYViWyUQHJwduEaXQ-chMhJ-A\u0022 height=\u0022973\u0022 src=\u0022https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/A49v0RGqHPTy2DDTo9L4ij9vv1BYy3vcMUIkcKfevMAheTDVCxlnTlbB-7Ueb6dlHSjnF3Ig1n7GI37RRqQIAce8QUI2b-9JMM_ixl9998aGwwn3OxnUCqYViWyUQHJwduEaXQ-chMhJ-A\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027;font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027;font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo is there anything doable about this problem?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-06T14:04:22Z\u0022 title=\u002206/06/2018 02:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 6, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Ultimate Steve\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T17:11:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow are you resizing the pictures?\u00A0 Are you just dragging the little boxes on the edge?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou should be able to edit the pictures\u0027 properties by either double clicking the image, or holding ctrl and right clicking on the image.\u00A0 This lets you set a w/h pixel value as well as decide whether it forces aspect ratio or not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]